comment:
AH‚Äôs own personal issues aren‚Äôt shared ‚Äúrelationship‚Äù issues and therefore not a ‚Äútwo to tango‚Äù problem. Dealing with Cluster B people. Ugh. It is a true nightmare and getting a lot of ignorant folks to say well, it takes two...is just what they do. Tho in this case, notice how it goes from eh, maybe it‚Äôs not all her. Maybe it‚Äôs both. But in the end, it‚Äôs all getting dumped on JD and somehow it gets totally flipped onto it being his fault entirely. JD himself has used the word ‚Äúperverse‚Äù and he is absolutely correct. This is standard protocol for these types of abusers tho, who would do ANYTHING to skirt all accountability and all consequences for their own bad behaviors toward others. Particularly when it‚Äôs abuse. 

They also often do what is called love bombing, and they love to do it when someone is at a vulnerable place in their lives or when they can find someone who is unusually kind and tolerant. Mostly tho, they are just calculating what benefits them and only them the most. (Aka. Money. Fame. Status. Etc). So they inundate their targets with a shit ton of overwhelming affection and attention and mirror them claiming to be some perfect ‚Äúsoul mate.‚Äù Then they get the hook in and get the other person addicted to them. This happens a lot more than many people would like to think. Male or female. So when they‚Äôre good and addicted, they start in with all the abuse and devaluing and the target is totally thrown off balance. I‚Äôm going into great detail bcuz I‚Äôve lived it, starting with a narcissistic step father, tho I think I‚Äôd put AH in the malignant borderline category, which isn‚Äôt all that diff from a narc.

He says "She deserves to have her baby overhauled" and then goes on to talk passionately about the car like it's an extension of her. How disrespectful. comment: The attention is not on her and she is not being asked her opinion so she is not interested.  She makes no bones about showing with her body language that she is not interested.  This is typical narcissistic behavior - they are the star of the show and everyone else is in a supporting role.  When people don't treat them this way then they think there is something wrong.  She is also letting JD know that she has no interest in what he is saying. The question on why JD got involved with AH I believe is because her looks and fake persona initially swept him off his feet.  Then bit by bit the narcissists actual nasty, malicious personality come through.  What they tend to do is brainwash their victim into believing that their change in attitude is the victim's fault.  This leaves the victim in a state of confusion and they then try to find out what is wrong and try to get the narcissist to return to their original persona.  This won't  happen because the original persona was fake.  So when you hear JD continuing to try to reason with AH and her continual arguing and blaming him, this is what happened.  The moment when JD told AH 'you know what Amber, your not real.  You were just something in my head'.  That was the moment it clicked and he realized that it was not his fault and her original persona was fake.

comment: You made a good point; when you are in the midst of a relationship a lot of times you are trying to see the best in them.  Especially when it's a new relationship.  You don't normally go into a relationship with the thought of "Let's see how many faults I can find " also many times,  especially if you have never been involved with a person who is abusive you start out blaming yourself and questioning what you can change to make it work.  There are so many different things that people do to try to hold onto a relationship even when abuse is happening and it's a horrible situation for the people involved.  Even when you are done and ready to leave the abuser,  you will remember that at one time you cared/loved this person and you will try to not hurt them.  Abuse is a terrible thing that unless you have been through it,  you just can't imagine how destroying it is on so many levels. Thank you for all of your insights and great videos!
